Pinoy is a slang that caught on for Filipinos(with the y appendaged after Fili''pino''Y) to denote their country of origin and background.

Kabayan is the proper way to address fellow Filipinos(To mean "comes from the same town")  

Noypi is a colloquial variation of pinoy(backwards) 

FLIP was thought of being derogatory although debatable. It was said to have been coined by American Soldiers from World War II to supposedly mean "Fucking Little Island Person ' although its true origin may be disputed, an urban legend.  

North American Filipinos have loosely used FLIP to describe their background. A more plausible origin of the term comes from the word  ''Filipino'' shortened, sound distinct.

